## Environment Management with uv

- Use `uv` for all Python environment and dependency management
- Create virtual environment: `uv venv`
- Install dependencies: `uv pip install -r requirements.txt`
- Sync dependencies: `uv pip sync requirements.txt`
- Add new package: `uv pip install package-name` then update requirements.txt
- Activate: `source .venv/bin/activate` (Linux/Mac) or `.venv\Scripts\activate` (Windows)
- Run Streamlit: `uv run streamlit run app.py` (runs in uv-managed environment)

## Python 3.10 Standards

- Use type hints for all function parameters and return types
- Prefer `from __future__ import annotations` for forward references
- Use `match/case` statements where appropriate (Python 3.10+)
- Use dataclasses for data structures when appropriate
- Leverage structural pattern matching for complex conditionals

## Streamlit Best Practices

- Use `st.set_page_config()` at the top of each page
- Implement session state for maintaining user progress through study sections
- Use `@st.cache_data` for expensive data loading operations (parsing study plan)
- Use `@st.cache_resource` for expensive object initialization (e.g., model loading)
- Prefer `st.columns()` for layout over deprecated `st.beta_columns()`
- Use `st.expander()` for collapsible sections (objectives, reading lists)
- Implement proper error handling with `st.error()` and `try/except`
- Use `st.markdown()` with HTML for rich formatting when needed
- Organize code into reusable functions/classes
- Use `st.sidebar` for navigation and progress tracking

## Code Style

- Follow PEP 8 conventions
- Maximum line length: 100 characters (Streamlit-friendly)
- Use descriptive variable names
- Add docstrings to all functions and classes (Google style)
- Group imports: standard library, third-party, local imports

## Study Plan Integration

- Parse study plan content from [SnowPro_GenAI_Study_Plan_V2.md](mdc:docs/SnowPro_GenAI_Study_Plan_V2.md)
- Structure content by sections and domains (7 main sections)
- Link to official Snowflake documentation URLs from study plan
- Track user progress through study sections using session state
- Display time estimates from study plan (e.g., "3.0 h" for Domain 1.0)
- Organize by domain weights: 1.0 (26%), 2.0 (40%), 3.0 (22%), 4.0 (12%)
- Include practice tasks and assignments from study plan
- Reference "Exam-Safe" vs "Latest/Preview" distinctions from study plan

## Snowflake Cortex AI Patterns

When implementing Snowflake integration:
- Use `snowflake.connector` or `snowflake-snowpark-python` for connections
- Store credentials in environment variables (never hardcode)
- Implement connection pooling for efficiency
- Use parameterized queries for all SQL operations
- Follow Snowflake RBAC patterns (CORTEX_USER, COPILOT_USER roles)
- Handle cross-region inference configuration properly
- Prefer AISQL functions (AI_COMPLETE, AI_PARSE_DOCUMENT, AI_EXTRACT) over deprecated PREDICT paths

## Error Handling

- Always handle Snowflake connection errors gracefully
- Provide user-friendly error messages
- Log errors appropriately (consider using Python logging)
- Implement retry logic for transient failures
- Validate user inputs before API calls

## Performance

- Cache parsed study plan content with `@st.cache_data`
- Lazy load pages and heavy content
- Use Streamlit's native caching mechanisms
- Optimize images and assets
- Minimize external API calls
